<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Headlines signalling Arsenal signing overseas centre backs normally send shivers down the spine of the club’s long-suffering fans but the Gunners may well have struck gold with Gabriel.</p>

<p>The 22-year-old Brazilian - full name Gabriel dos Santos Magalhaes - had not played for six months before making his Premier League debut.</p>

<p>But there were no signs of rust with him scoring a goal and delivering a towering performance at the heart of Mikel Arteta’s back three.</p>

<p>Arsenal may have struck gold after debutant Gabriel Magalhaes impressed against Fulham</p>

<p>‘Gabriel has come in, the system has changed and they look comfortable,’ said another classy central defender, Rio Ferdinand, on BT Sport. </p>

<p>‘He can only be confident from this.’</p>

<p>Gabriel has been highly rated since making his debut in Brazil’s Serie B with Avai as a 16-year-old - well, maybe not by everyone.</p>

<p>The one notable manager who didn’t fancy him is current Leeds boss Marcelo Bielsa who, when at Lille, sent Gabriel out on loan to rival French club Troyes.</p>

<p>The 22-year-old defender netted in the win at Fulham and delivered a towering performance</p>
